<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Security Posture Assessment — {{CLIENT_NAME}}</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:opsz,wght@9..144,400;9..144,600;9..144,900&family=IBM+Plex+Sans:wght@300;400;500;600&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
:root {
  --ink:        #1a1a1a;
  --ink-soft:   #3d3d3d;
  --ink-mute:   #6b6b6b;
  --paper:      #fafaf7;
  --paper-alt:  #f2f0e9;
  --rule:       #d9d5c8;
  --accent:     #7a2e2e;
  --accent-alt: #a84242;
  --critical:   #8b1a1a;
  --high:       #b85400;
  --medium:     #8a6d00;
  --low:        #546e3a;
  --pass:       #4a6b4a;
}

* { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

html { font-size: 16px; }

body {
  font-family: "IBM Plex Sans", system-ui, sans-serif;
  font-weight: 300;
  font-size: 1rem;
  line-height: 1.65;
  color: var(--ink);
  background: var(--paper);
  padding: 0;
}

.page {
  max-width: 920px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 4rem 3rem 6rem;
}

/* ========== Masthead ========== */

.masthead {
  border-top: 3px solid var(--ink);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink);
  padding: 2.5rem 0 2rem;
  margin-bottom: 3rem;
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
  gap: 2rem;
  align-items: end;
}

.masthead .eyebrow {
  font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.18em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--ink-mute);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.masthead h1 {
  font-family: "Fraunces", Georgia, serif;
  font-weight: 400;
  font-size: 3.25rem;
  line-height: 1.05;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  color: var(--ink);
}

.masthead h1 em {
  font-style: italic;
  font-weight: 400;
}

.masthead .meta {
  text-align: right;
  font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  line-height: 1.8;
  color: var(--ink-soft);
}

.masthead .meta .label {
  color: var(--ink-mute);
  padding-right: 0.5rem;
}

/* ========== Score block ========== */

.score-block {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
  gap: 3rem;
  align-items: center;
  padding: 3rem 0;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  margin-bottom: 3rem;
}

.grade {
  font-family: "Fraunces", serif;
  font-weight: 900;
  font-size: 9rem;
  line-height: 0.85;
  color: var(--accent);
  font-feature-settings: "ss01";
}

.score-detail .score-pct {
  font-family: "Fraunces", serif;
  font-size: 2rem;
  font-weight: 400;
  color: var(--ink);
  display: inline-block;
  margin-right: 1rem;
}

.score-detail .score-frac {
  font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: var(--ink-mute);
}

.score-caption {
  font-family: "Fraunces", serif;
  font-size: 1.15rem;
  font-style: italic;
  color: var(--ink-soft);
  max-width: 36ch;
  margin-top: 0.75rem;
  line-height: 1.5;
}

/* ========== Stats strip ========== */

.stats {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
  gap: 0;
  margin-bottom: 4rem;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
}

.stat {
  padding: 1.5rem 1rem;
  border-right: 1px solid var(--rule);
  text-align: left;
}

.stat:last-child { border-right: none; }

.stat .n {
  font-family: "Fraunces", serif;
  font-size: 2.4rem;
  font-weight: 400;
  line-height: 1;
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
}

.stat.critical .n { color: var(--critical); }
.stat.high .n     { color: var(--high); }
.stat.passed .n   { color: var(--pass); }

.stat .label {
  font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  color: var(--ink-mute);
}

/* ========== Sections ========== */

section {
  margin-bottom: 4rem;
}

h2 {
  font-family: "Fraunces", serif;
  font-weight: 400;
  font-size: 1.85rem;
  letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  color: var(--ink);
}

.section-lede {
  font-family: "Fraunces", serif;
  font-style: italic;
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  color: var(--ink-soft);
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
  max-width: 60ch;
  line-height: 1.55;
}

.section-divider {
  height: 1px;
  background: var(--ink);
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
  opacity: 0.8;
}

/* ========== Findings ========== */

.finding {
  border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  padding: 1.75rem 0 1.5rem;
  position: relative;
}

.finding:first-of-type { border-top: 1px solid var(--ink); }

.finding-head {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.75rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
}

.sev-badge {
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem;
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--paper);
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
}

.sev-badge.sev-critical { background: var(--critical); }
.sev-badge.sev-high     { background: var(--high); }
.sev-badge.sev-medium   { background: var(--medium); }
.sev-badge.sev-low      { background: var(--low); }

.ctrl-id {
  color: var(--ink);
  font-weight: 500;
}

.ctrl-cat {
  color: var(--ink-mute);
}

.ctrl-cat::before {
  content: "/ ";
  color: var(--rule);
  padding-right: 0.1rem;
}

.finding-title {
  font-family: "Fraunces", serif;
  font-size: 1.35rem;
  font-weight: 400;
  line-height: 1.3;
  color: var(--ink);
  margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
  max-width: 65ch;
}

.finding-details {
  color: var(--ink-soft);
  max-width: 68ch;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  line-height: 1.65;
}

.finding-rem {
  border-left: 2px solid var(--accent);
  padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1rem;
  margin-top: 0.75rem;
  font-size: 0.92rem;
  max-width: 68ch;
}

.finding-rem summary {
  cursor: pointer;
  font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  color: var(--accent);
  font-weight: 500;
  user-select: none;
}

.finding-rem summary:hover { color: var(--accent-alt); }

.finding-rem p {
  margin-top: 0.75rem;
  color: var(--ink-soft);
  line-height: 1.6;
  white-space: pre-wrap;
}

.finding.sev-critical {
  background:
    linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(139,26,26,0.025) 0%, transparent 60%);
}

.no-findings {
  padding: 3rem 2rem;
  text-align: center;
  background: var(--paper-alt);
  border-left: 3px solid var(--pass);
  font-family: "Fraunces", serif;
  font-style: italic;
  color: var(--ink-soft);
}

/* ========== Exception table ========== */

table.exceptions {
  width: 100%;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  font-size: 0.92rem;
  margin-top: 1rem;
}

.exceptions th {
  text-align: left;
  padding: 0.75rem 0.9rem;
  font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
  font-size: 0.7rem;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  color: var(--ink-mute);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink);
  font-weight: 500;
}

.exceptions td {
  padding: 1rem 0.9rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  vertical-align: top;
  color: var(--ink-soft);
}

.exceptions td.mono, .exceptions .mono {
  font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  color: var(--ink);
}

.exceptions td.empty {
  text-align: center;
  color: var(--ink-mute);
  font-style: italic;
  padding: 2rem;
}

/* ========== Colophon ========== */

.colophon {
  margin-top: 6rem;
  padding-top: 2rem;
  border-top: 3px solid var(--ink);
  font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  color: var(--ink-mute);
  line-height: 1.8;
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 2rem;
}

.colophon strong {
  color: var(--ink);
  font-weight: 500;
}

/* ========== Print ========== */

@media print {
  body { background: white; }
  .page { padding: 1.5rem; max-width: none; }
  .masthead h1 { font-size: 2.25rem; }
  .grade { font-size: 6rem; }
  .finding { break-inside: avoid; }
  .finding-rem[open] summary ~ * { display: block; }
  .finding-rem { break-inside: avoid; }
  details { break-inside: avoid; }
  details summary { display: none; }
  details > p { display: block !important; }
  a { color: inherit; text-decoration: none; }
}

/* ========== Responsive ========== */

@media (max-width: 700px) {
  .page { padding: 2rem 1.25rem 3rem; }
  .masthead { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .masthead .meta { text-align: left; }
  .masthead h1 { font-size: 2.25rem; }
  .score-block { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; }
  .grade { font-size: 6rem; }
  .stats { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  .stat { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .stat:nth-child(odd) { border-right: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .colophon { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="page">

  <header class="masthead">
    <div>
      <div class="eyebrow">Security Posture Assessment</div>
      <h1>{{CLIENT_NAME}}<br><em>Tier&nbsp;1 Baseline</em></h1>
    </div>
    <div class="meta">
      <div><span class="label">Date</span>{{RUN_DATE}}</div>
      <div><span class="label">Baseline</span>v{{BASELINE_VERSION}}</div>
      <div><span class="label">Run ID</span>{{RUN_ID}}</div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="score-block">
    <div class="grade">{{GRADE}}</div>
    <div class="score-detail">
      <span class="score-pct">{{SCORE_PCT}}%</span>
      <span class="score-frac">{{PASSED}} of {{TOTAL}} controls passed</span>
      <p class="score-caption">A directional indicator of configuration strength against the SMB Tier&nbsp;1 baseline. Not a compliance attestation.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="stats">
    <div class="stat critical">
      <span class="n">{{CRITICAL_FAILURES}}</span>
      <span class="label">Critical</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stat high">
      <span class="n">{{HIGH_FAILURES}}</span>
      <span class="label">High</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stat">
      <span class="n">{{FAILED}}</span>
      <span class="label">Total Failing</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stat passed">
      <span class="n">{{PASSED}}</span>
      <span class="label">Passing</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stat">
      <span class="n">{{EXCEPTED}}</span>
      <span class="label">Excepted</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section>
    <h2>Findings</h2>
    <p class="section-lede">
      Failures are ordered by severity. Critical and high-severity items close real attack paths and should be remediated first.
    </p>
    <div class="section-divider"></div>

    {{FINDINGS_HTML}}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Acknowledged Exceptions</h2>
    <p class="section-lede">
      Controls deliberately not enforced, with a documented reason and approver. These are risk acceptances, not passes.
    </p>
    <div class="section-divider"></div>

    <table class="exceptions">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Control</th>
          <th>Name</th>
          <th>Reason</th>
          <th>Approved by</th>
          <th>Expires</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {{EXCEPTIONS_HTML}}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What this report is — and isn't</h2>
    <div class="section-divider"></div>
    <p style="max-width: 68ch; color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.7;">
      This assessment measures your Microsoft 365 and Windows endpoint configuration against a curated baseline sized for small and mid-sized organizations. It does not measure attacker behavior, employee behavior, or the effectiveness of licensed security products at runtime. A passing score reflects good hygiene, not invulnerability. A failing score reflects improvement opportunities, not imminent breach.
    </p>
    <p style="max-width: 68ch; color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.7; margin-top: 1rem;">
      Controls deferred to the Tier&nbsp;2 baseline (available separately) address more advanced threats that require dedicated operational capacity to maintain. Organizations with compliance obligations, in-house IT staff, or higher risk tolerance should consider the enhanced baseline.
    </p>
  </section>

  <footer class="colophon">
    <div>
      <strong>SMB Hardening Essentials</strong><br>
      Tier&nbsp;1 Baseline v{{BASELINE_VERSION}}<br>
      Generated {{RUN_DATE}}
    </div>
    <div>
      Assessed with Maester and HardeningKitty<br>
      Mapped directionally to CIS Controls v8 IG1<br>
      Run ID: {{RUN_ID}}
    </div>
  </footer>

</div>
</body>
</html>
